<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>Graphics APIs offer different levels and kinds of information. The only value that is available across all APIs is the <db:link xlink:href="qrhidriverinfo.xml#deviceName-var">deviceName</db:link>, which is a freetext description of the physical device, adapter, or is a combination of the strings reported for <db:code>GL_VENDOR</db:code> + <db:code>GL_RENDERER</db:code> + <db:code>GL_VERSION</db:code>. The <db:link xlink:href="qrhidriverinfo.xml#deviceId-var">deviceId</db:link> is always 0 for OpenGL. <db:link xlink:href="qrhidriverinfo.xml#vendorId-var">vendorId</db:link> is always 0 for OpenGL and Metal. <db:link xlink:href="qrhidriverinfo.xml#deviceType-var">deviceType</db:link> is always <db:link xlink:href="qrhidriverinfo.xml#DeviceType-enum">UnknownDevice</db:link> for OpenGL and Direct 3D.</db:para>
<db:note>
<db:para>This is a RHI API with limited compatibility guarantees, see <db:link xlink:href="qrhi.xml">QRhi</db:link> for details.</db:para>
</db:note>
</db:section>
